= Tab Plugin For Redmine

A plugin to allow users to create a new Redmine tab and embed content from an iframe

== INSTALLATION == 

To install from git: 

$ cd {RAILS_ROOT}/vendor/plugins 
$ git clone git://github.com/jamtur01/redmine_tab.git

== INSTRUCTIONS ==

1. This will allow you to create a tab that references a custom iframe.  You will need to go to
'Admin -> Custom fields -> Project' and create a field of type 'Long text' for the iframe.  

2. Select the field you've created in your plugin configuration by selecting Plugins -> Tab Plugin and clicking Configure.  
 
3. Inside your project you will need to add your iframe link as the value of the field you've selected.  For example to imbed Google:

<iframe src="http://www.google.com/" style="border: 0" width="800" height="600" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe>

4. Then using the Modules tab select the Tab module to add the new tab to your menu.

